==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Xanthidium
<hw>Xan*thid"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Xanthidia</plw> <pr>(?)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>xanqo`s</grk> yellow.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus
of minute unicellular algae of the desmids. These algae have a rounded
shape and are armed with glochidiate or branched aculei. Several species
occur in ditches, and others are found fossil in flint or
hornstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

